Then I drove all the way out to waterford to "watch" michael bowl. He didnt get to, it was kind of sad and he looked real upset. But they won so that was sweet. Oh man can Jeremy bowl! Then there were these crazy boys from another school just yelling and cheering. Oh man, they were funny.

I got into a tickle fight with michael. Then we ganged up on rachael and she really started to spaz out. It was kind of Crazy. I felt kind of weird there because it was gregs house and everything... Him being the Ex, Michael and I being there together. I dont know. Kind of strange. I kept feeling like I was being watched or something. Lauren was being kind of strange taking pictures of me every second. I dont know why she was trying to hide it because I knew that she was taking them. Oh well I dont really care. 

Friday: Michael came over for a little while after I was done babysitting. I made 40 dollars that night. 10 dollars a hour isnt that bad. Well michael came over and we watched Bad Boys II. It was a funny movie! 

Saturday: Chirstmas Eve! I went to my Aunt Lori's house. Everyone got drunk. Nick and I exchanged gifts this year. I wraped his present in a tin can, nailed it shut, wrapped it, put it in a tampon box, wrapped that, put that in a shoe box and duck taped it and then wrapped that, put that box into a bigger box. duck taped the whole entire box and wrapped it with like ten layers of wrapping paper. He had such a hard time opening the present. This year we had a 26 dollar limit... yeah it got cut in half 2 times. so he worked really hard for 26 dollars. Nick got me a shirt from abercrombie and fitch and my aunt got me a leatard for dance class. Oh and we opened all of our presents when we got home.

Sunday: Chistmas! Got up opened some stuff in my stocking. Didnt have any presents under the tree since we opened them all up the day before. I got a Skagen watch, some rings, Berkinstock shoes, a clicker for my TV (remote control) and a bucn of clothes and some marching band pictures. It was nice. I got everything that I wanted except for socks! Michael got me a night out on the town (dinner in greektown and tickets to the red wings game) Hes such a sweety. And he got me a picture of him and I from over the summer and a little teddy bear.  Well then I went to church, then off to my aunt vicky's house. They have this 10 dollar gift exchange every year. My uncle jim always brings the funniest presents. This year he brought 10 loafs of bread with a jar of peanut butter and jelly. It was so funny.

Well... yesterday really kicked us in the ass. but hey, its only two points! Its not really our fault anyways! They cant expect us to do better when they take the whole last song and change everything two days before we perform. But I thought that it was one of my best performaces, and thats all that really matters. I didnt fall, and I didnt drop my flag! So I was happy. I got the last broccoli soup too! I sat with michael. I couldnt stop laughing because he couldnt stop burping. I went out for awards and froze my ass off too! Nick, Nate, Justin, Leah, Katie, and I decided that we're going to do a "Wave" for awards next week! Its going to be sweet. 

After that was all over with... OMG the bus ride home was great! Seniors in the back being dirty! Taking pictures, Adrienne and Zac doing only god knows what, Justin being all cranky, Zac being just funny, and Leah getting spanked by Jeremy. It was the best night ever! Then there is Josh telling me that I have to be a good girlfriend. HA, too bad I dont have a boyfriend to be good to! Then Josh said "what does that mean" 
"I dont know Josh, for all I know I'm just someone that he makes out with"
"But you're his girlfriend arnt you?" 
"Umm... sure?"
"you mean he hasnt even asked you yet?... So basically he just assumes that you're his girlfriend"
"Basically..."
"so you kind of are and you kind of arnt?" 
"Well see josh... since he hasnt asked me to be his gf... that means that I can just go and make out with anyone because he hasnt asked for that commitment"
"YOU WOULD REALLY DO THAT TO HIM?"
"fuck no, I like michael!" 

Besides having boy craziness going on... bus rides are the best! AND THIS TIME WE DIDNT HAVE TO SIT WITH THE DAMN DRUMMERS...
HEY GUYS, I WON!!! perfect attendence all the way! Woot for 15 whole dollars! Who wants to go out?

When you fell like you've been fucked over in everything that you worked so hard for... and you put everything else to the side (like all your homework) and then at the last minute they change everything, it feels like you have nothing to show for it. I used to care, until people... who are rookies decided that seniors arn't cool, and they dont mean anything... even if they are a section leader... but that doesnt mean anything. 

I remember when I was a freshamn, we respected the upper classman. We didnt think twice if they told us to do something. If they told us to do something we did it, without complaning or having a little section of underclassman trying to rebel because we had respect for our upperclassman. THAT YEAR WE MADE IT TO STATES, and we didnt even try. But now, If a senior wants the underclassman to do something for the benefit of them... they basically say "eff that, Im not doing that. you cant tell me what to do, you're not my mom, ive been working just as hard as you have... if not harder." WELL YOU KNOW WHAT.... IN THE GUARD, THE SENIORS ARE YOUR MOMS! And what we say, usually goes! 
Too much drama has been going on in guard the past few weeks.... and now that so much has changed... and i wasnt even there to learn what changed because i was at a funneral home crying because Grandma Betty died... I COULD SERIOUSLY CARE LESS NOW! If i could, I would hand in my poles, and spend my time bringing up my unaccepted grade in AP Biology, and try to go to bed before 2am and see how it makes me feel in the morning! But i cant because then ill fail band too... and if you fail band that means that there is something seriously wrong with you! I just wish one day that I wouldnt wake up with bags under my eyes, and then have some random girls come up to me in the hall complaning about guard... Ive tried too hard to just keep all my anger inside of me, and just deal with all the changes... but you know what, I CANT BE A LEADER IF PEOPLE WONT LET ME BE! and im pretty sure that every senior in guard feels the same way. So for now on, keep your crap at the door, and just come to guard and do what is told. Thats what they told me freshamn year and ive sticked to it for the most part. Dont let wally and mr. lewis get to you, and just have fun for the rest of the year. I joined guard not just for a grade in band... but because i have a blast being with all of you girls and basically kicking ass. But color guard is taking over my  life... and becoming something that i dont want to do. So lets just make it fun again and forget about the competition part... even though thats kind of a big deal... ok lets try to do both.

Ok... when you put your shit in a nice little pile in a courner of a room and you come back after awards and you are fucking cold... you kind of want your fucking cloak! and you dont want to come to find all of your shit spread all across the room because girls went through it to find a cloak that they can wear that doesnt belong to them... so basically for now on if you're fucking cold and you need a cloak... BRING IT FROM HOME OR GO FIND ONE IN THE GUARD ROOM THAT ISNT USED, OR ASK SOMEONE IF YOU CAN BORROW IT. 

DONT GO THROUGH PEOPLES SHIT WHEN THEY ARE PASSING OUT AWARDS FREEZING THEIR ASSES OFF!

AND I WANT MY CLOAK BACK, and if I keep getting fucked over like this at every damn practice and at every damn thing that we have to do then im just going to hand in my poles and say fuck this... back to AP Biology homework!

Just one of those days when you dont even have time to think! 

I'm going to the movies tomorrow with Michael and some friends... what should we go see? 

Nick wants to see "Just like Heaven" but Rachael doesnt want to... and I dont think that Michael wants to either... he didnt tell me that... but that movie is kind of mushy... so...yeah
